                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/3569: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ellis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-04-13T10:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1925—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Referring to the Department’s telegram of April 11, 4 p.m. Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs assures me that his Government will do everything possible to
                    stabilize conditions on Honduras frontier. He states that General Ferrera<note
                        n="17" xml:id="d276fn17">Gen. Gregorio Ferrera, Honduran exile in
                        Guatemala.</note> who is now concentrated here intends to leave for Mexico
                    soon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ellis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
